1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,180
♫ When romance is too insignificant ♫

2
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:21,680
♫ But I can't stop missing you, like a bad cold ♫

3
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:28,300
♫ Drifting in a deserted island, where feelings have no reception ♫

4
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:32,160
♫ Have you been well? ♫

5
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:36,260
♫ Don't worry, I'll be fine ♫

6
00:00:36,260 --> 00:00:39,510
♫ Don't worry, I can't fall asleep ♫

7
00:00:39,510 --> 00:00:46,860
♫ Don't worry, I can't get used to this lonely world ♫

8
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:53,680
♫ Hitting the pause button, leaving your side ♫

9
00:00:53,680 --> 00:01:00,650
♫ Letting the memories migrate to that day of happiness ♫

10
00:01:00,650 --> 00:01:07,020
♫ I'm trying hard to smile as I say goodbye to you ♫

11
00:01:07,020 --> 00:01:12,890
♫ I recall and long for the happiness you want, I can make it happen ♫

12
00:01:12,890 --> 00:01:16,070
♫ Can't hold back the tears, leading to regret ♫

13
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:22,040
♫ Losing you whom I love, heartbreak is inevitable ♫

14
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:28,710
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

15
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:31,460
[Lost Romance]

16
00:01:31,460 --> 00:01:33,610
No matter what year it is, everyone needs an overbearing CEO.

17
00:01:33,610 --> 00:01:35,320
Overbearing CEOs can't die!

18
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:40,200
I'll be happy if this Situ Aoran can just help us get this month's bonus.

19
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:44,760
God, please give me an overbearing CEO!

20
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:48,350
Just go to sleep. Anything can happen in a dream.

21
00:01:49,540 --> 00:01:54,330
In Dad's will, it is clearly written that the entire Tianliang Group will be left with He Tianxing.

22
00:01:54,330 --> 00:01:57,670
We can't just sit and await our deaths.

23
00:01:57,670 --> 00:01:59,680
Qiaozhi!

24
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:01,320
Why is the news saying that it was an accident?

25
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:03,530
It clearly wasn't from what I saw.

26
00:02:03,530 --> 00:02:06,250
He Tianxing! You're okay now?

27
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:08,720
It's so great to see that you've recovered!

28
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:12,820
Woman, you're in this building, but you don't know who I am?

29
00:02:12,820 --> 00:02:15,130
Zheng Xiao'en, you don't know who Situ Aoran is?

30
00:02:15,130 --> 00:02:16,610
Situ Aoran?

31
00:02:16,610 --> 00:02:19,020
CEO, You're So Naughty?

32
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:22,430
Zheng Xiao'en, if it's not in your dreams, traversing time and space, or being near death,

33
00:02:22,430 --> 00:02:24,450
would you get the chance to be this close to He Tianxing?

34
00:02:24,450 --> 00:02:27,650
Romance novels all have their formulas.

35
00:02:27,650 --> 00:02:30,250
As long as I can figure out the formula,

36
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:34,020
I can make you the female lead even if you're not the female lead.

37
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:37,130
I just don't believe that I can't change my fortunes.

38
00:02:37,130 --> 00:02:38,500
Be careful!

39
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:39,970
The feelings between the male and female leads

40
00:02:39,970 --> 00:02:44,130
get warmer and warmer every time the hero saves the damsel-in-distress.

41
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:46,760
So if I want to get in between them,

42
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:53,110
I have to create a place for me in this cycle!

43
00:02:55,420 --> 00:02:59,660
Blood!

44
00:02:59,660 --> 00:03:02,210
Doctor!

45
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:12,000
[Lost Romance]

46
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,720
[Chapter Three]

47
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,650
Her nose has stopped bleeding now.

48
00:03:23,650 --> 00:03:26,570
We didn't find any other symptoms after examining her.

49
00:03:26,570 --> 00:03:28,980
She might have gotten the nosebleed because the air in the hospital room is rather dry.

50
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:32,010
We'll add a humidifier and check on her later.

51
00:03:32,010 --> 00:03:34,110
Thank you, Doctor.

52
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:44,010
You... you scared me to death.

53
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,710
What are you doing?

54
00:03:57,420 --> 00:04:00,220
I'm applying some medication.

55
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,150
Or did you think I was doing my personal care routine?

56
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:08,670
I'm asking you... what was that elegant dolphin dive all about?

57
00:04:08,670 --> 00:04:10,830
Just...

58
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:15,310
My eyes were blurry, and I thought there was a box of face masks on the floor.

59
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:17,530
- Face masks?
- That's right!

60
00:04:17,530 --> 00:04:19,800
The masks that even rich people can't buy.

61
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:24,170
The kind that shines brightly no matter where it is placed.

62
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,380
You didn't see it?

63
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:28,430
No.

64
00:04:28,430 --> 00:04:30,530
Oh...

65
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:35,770
Are you okay? Are you not feeling well?

66
00:04:35,770 --> 00:04:38,330
I'm fine. I feel great.

67
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:42,130
Do I look like the kind of person who is sickly and delicate*?
(*Xiao'en uses a phrase which has Chuchu's name in it.)

68
00:04:42,130 --> 00:04:44,090
Xiao'en.

69
00:04:46,790 --> 00:04:51,850
Murphy's Law. When you talk about someone, she appears.

70
00:04:51,850 --> 00:04:53,530
How is your injury?

71
00:04:53,530 --> 00:04:56,090
I'm really worried about you.

72
00:04:56,090 --> 00:04:59,190
I'm fine. It was just a scratch.

73
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:07,970
You probably got scared by all the chaos earlier, right?

74
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:14,710
I'm fine. I'm just worried about Xiao'en.

75
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:18,730
Thank you. I'm okay now.

76
00:05:18,730 --> 00:05:20,460
I'm really sorry.

77
00:05:20,460 --> 00:05:24,330
You fell because you were trying to warn me about the cart, right?

78
00:05:24,330 --> 00:05:28,740
Don't think that way. I'm not that good of a person.

79
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,800
Don't blame yourself.

80
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:38,830
Xiao'en... got into an accident just now... because she had some hallucinations.

81
00:05:40,010 --> 00:05:44,380
This look. This facial expression. This smile.

82
00:05:44,380 --> 00:05:48,250
These pink bubbles that can be seen by everyone other than the actual people involved.

83
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:50,950
What's going on?

84
00:05:52,460 --> 00:05:54,810
I know.

85
00:05:55,850 --> 00:05:59,010
I'll let you rest and not bother you anymore.

86
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:13,690
Stop staring.

87
00:06:13,690 --> 00:06:16,340
Let me, the expert in the school of CEOs, tell you.

88
00:06:16,340 --> 00:06:19,720
The male and female leads only have eyes for each other.

89
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:22,920
Don't be sad.

90
00:06:38,070 --> 00:06:40,220
The preparation work is pretty much done.

91
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:42,930
It's pretty much done. We can start checking everything soon.

92
00:06:42,930 --> 00:06:45,230
There shouldn't be any problems.

93
00:06:52,310 --> 00:06:54,990
Don't you think that woman is really weird?

94
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:01,650
You mean Zheng Xiao'en?

95
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:04,350
Yes, her.

96
00:07:05,370 --> 00:07:07,810
She's acting so sneaky.

97
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:11,650
She is pretty strange.

98
00:07:11,650 --> 00:07:13,950
You didn't know?

99
00:07:13,950 --> 00:07:18,740
She pranked Chuchu in the bathroom and poured water all over her.

100
00:07:18,740 --> 00:07:22,360
For someone to play such dirty tricks so openly at the company,

101
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:25,700
I won't be the least bit surprised if she does something more ridiculous the next time.

102
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,430
She doesn't seem like that type of person.

103
00:07:27,430 --> 00:07:31,950
Not seeming like it and not actually being that type of person are two different things.

104
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:35,260
I think there must be some sort of misunderstanding in the middle.

105
00:07:35,260 --> 00:07:37,210
I don't think so.

106
00:07:39,630 --> 00:07:44,460
Hey! Hey! Hey! Get out of the way!

107
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:45,940
Don't touch this. Let the professional handle this.

108
00:07:45,940 --> 00:07:47,660
If there's an electrical fault, you could lose your life.

109
00:07:47,660 --> 00:07:50,480
Okay.

110
00:08:06,810 --> 00:08:09,460
Hey, this is such a simple task. Just let me handle it.

111
00:08:09,460 --> 00:08:12,010
You don't have to trouble yourself with it.

112
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:17,680
Hey! Be careful! This is very dangerous!

113
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:20,090
Be careful not to get burned.

114
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:26,840
Miss! I'm begging you to please stop doing things.

115
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,450
Go rest on the side.

116
00:08:28,450 --> 00:08:30,470
Remember to stay away from the chandeliers.

117
00:08:30,470 --> 00:08:32,740
Okay.

118
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:40,830
Zheng Xiao'en, what are you doing?

119
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:43,120
Organizing the dried flowers.

120
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:45,480
Dried flowers...

121
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:48,600
Who asked you about this?

122
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:51,270
What's wrong with you today? Feeling charitable?

123
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:53,850
You're doing all of Chuchu's tasks.

124
00:08:53,850 --> 00:08:57,700
Let me ask you, did you finish all of your own tasks?

125
00:09:07,850 --> 00:09:10,020
Careful!

126
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,410
[Emergency Room]

127
00:09:51,410 --> 00:09:54,060
Aoran, are you okay?

128
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:57,200
It's a small injury. I'm fine.

129
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:00,000
CEO, I'm sorry.

130
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,390
It's all my fault. My clumsiness resulted in you getting injured.

131
00:10:03,390 --> 00:10:05,970
Why am I so useless?

132
00:10:07,780 --> 00:10:10,760
I won't allow you to say that about yourself.

133
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:12,970
It's a man's responsibility to protect a woman.

134
00:10:12,970 --> 00:10:15,940
It's my destiny to protect you.

135
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:19,160
You didn't do anything wrong, okay?

136
00:10:23,330 --> 00:10:25,490
You didn't get hurt, right?

137
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:27,430
I'm fine.

138
00:10:29,590 --> 00:10:32,980
Chuchu needs to die!

139
00:10:35,650 --> 00:10:40,420
Sorry, CEO. We will thoroughly check everything tomorrow

140
00:10:40,420 --> 00:10:43,450
to make sure the appreciation banquet goes smoothly.

141
00:10:43,450 --> 00:10:46,910
If anything goes wrong tomorrow,

142
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:49,420
all of you can pack your bags and leave.

143
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:57,100
Okay. Make sure the wound doesn't touch water.

144
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:59,210
Thank you, Nurse.

145
00:10:59,210 --> 00:11:02,510
I'm so sorry to have troubled you.

146
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:07,660
Who does she think she is? The lady of the house?

147
00:11:09,310 --> 00:11:11,350
I'll leave the banquet to you.

148
00:11:11,350 --> 00:11:14,580
Chuchu experienced shock, so I'll take her home.

149
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:22,360
Will that be too inconvenient for you, CEO?

150
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:25,950
As long as I want to do it, it won't be an inconvenience.

151
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:31,010
Wait a minute!

152
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:41,450
I just want to say that

153
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:43,650
my house is on the way.

154
00:11:43,650 --> 00:11:45,790
You need me to take you back?

155
00:11:45,790 --> 00:11:48,270
Yes! How did you know?

156
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:51,040
Who gave you the courage

157
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:53,910
to treat me as a chauffeur?
(He refers to himself as "shaoye" which means "young master")

158
00:11:57,160 --> 00:12:01,700
Aiyo, I thought that since it was on the way...

159
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:04,440
Driving one person or two, it's still driving.

160
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,710
You should conserve energy and reduce carbon emissions.

161
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:10,990
Xiao'en was also injured.

162
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:15,280
She's also an employee of the company.

163
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:17,690
You won't play favorites, right?

164
00:12:21,410 --> 00:12:24,980
- Hurry, thank the CEO.
- Thank you, CEO!

165
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:39,620
I feel very sorry towards you, CEO.

166
00:12:39,620 --> 00:12:43,010
- If it weren't for me—
- The CEO would not have gotten hurt.

167
00:12:43,010 --> 00:12:45,100
It's my fault for being clumsy.

168
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:48,380
How can I be so useless?

169
00:12:48,380 --> 00:12:51,180
Aiyo, I just wanted to gently remind you that

170
00:12:51,180 --> 00:12:54,000
you already said that in the last scene.

171
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:59,940
Zheng Xiao'en, don't you have any manners?

172
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:04,620
Geez, can't everyone talk together?

173
00:13:06,350 --> 00:13:08,810
Where's your house? I'll take you back first.

174
00:13:08,810 --> 00:13:11,440
No! (in Korean) That won't do!

175
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:16,320
Chuchu is so fragile. We should take her home first.

176
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:20,230
Anything's fine with me as long as it's convenient for CEO.

177
00:13:32,460 --> 00:13:36,460
Thank you, CEO. You should get some rest.

178
00:13:37,770 --> 00:13:40,630
You go rest now.

179
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,510
Bye bye.

180
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:50,700
Bye bye.

181
00:14:04,940 --> 00:14:08,280
I haven't even told you where my house is!

182
00:14:15,410 --> 00:14:18,400
You're making me take the bus this late at night?

183
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,690
He's so handsome but so cold-hearted.

184
00:14:20,690 --> 00:14:22,820
I'm your diehard fan!

185
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:25,050
Don’t turn me into an anti-fan!

186
00:15:25,620 --> 00:15:28,340
You haven't eaten yet, right? What's wrong?

187
00:15:29,290 --> 00:15:31,810
It's so late.

188
00:15:31,810 --> 00:15:36,720
I'd be fine with Hong Kong-style cafe, but a French restaurant?

189
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:38,770
Is this reasonable?

190
00:15:39,620 --> 00:15:42,770
Aren't restaurants supposed to be there whenever you want to eat?

191
00:15:42,770 --> 00:15:45,440
Not just French cuisine restaurants, but also Japanese cuisine restaurants,

192
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:47,820
menu-less restaurants, and Russian restaurants.

193
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:49,570
They're all still open.

194
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:54,100
Or do you want to eat freshly delivered sashimi?

195
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,660
I'm fine.

196
00:15:57,210 --> 00:16:00,830
As expected, dreams have everything.

197
00:16:00,830 --> 00:16:03,650
You don't like any of these?

198
00:16:03,650 --> 00:16:06,080
It's not that I don't like it.

199
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:08,450
It's just that you can eat anything for a midnight snack.

200
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:10,990
Like NT$100 stir fry or popcorn chicken!

201
00:16:10,990 --> 00:16:13,740
Rice noodle soup. Cold noodles with miso soup.

202
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:16,950
It feels great to eat those at night.

203
00:16:18,210 --> 00:16:21,740
NT$100 stir fry? What is that?

204
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:28,510
You've never had NT$100 stir fry before?

205
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:33,320
It's not that I haven't had it before... I've never even heard of it.

206
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:37,730
And what's popcorn chicken?

207
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:44,140
Popcorn chicken is a Taiwanese staple, and you have to eat it with garlic and basil.

208
00:16:44,140 --> 00:16:47,720
It's insane that you've never heard of it.

209
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:54,970
Is there any place nearby that sells popcorn chicken?

210
00:16:58,990 --> 00:17:01,520
You've also never heard of popcorn chicken?

211
00:17:02,590 --> 00:17:07,680
What about danzai noodles, oyster omelettes, scallion pancakes, red bean cakes, or sponge cakes?

212
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:10,380
Is it good to drink?

213
00:17:14,410 --> 00:17:17,910
Let's just eat something French tonight.

214
00:17:19,610 --> 00:17:22,980
So it turns out that out of millions of romance novel worlds,

215
00:17:22,980 --> 00:17:25,780
there’s actually one that doesn’t have popcorn chicken?

216
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:29,710
Sure enough, they’re so poor that all they have is money.

217
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:34,640
Have you gone crazy with hunger?

218
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:37,930
Choose whatever you like. I'll pay today.

219
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:02,510
What a work of art.

220
00:18:02,510 --> 00:18:06,410
Sight, taste, and smell are satisfied all at once.

221
00:18:06,410 --> 00:18:09,350
You should carefully savor it.

222
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:12,340
Let's eat. I'll start.

223
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:29,380
You like Aoran, right?

224
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:35,650
It's not really that I like him.

225
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:38,890
What about you? You like Chuchu, don't you?

226
00:18:40,070 --> 00:18:41,870
I knew it.

227
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:49,270
What do you like about Aoran?

228
00:18:55,890 --> 00:18:58,280
Wow!

229
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:02,040
There's eye candy. Want to take a look?

230
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:04,910
No! It feels very perverted.

231
00:19:04,910 --> 00:19:06,970
Hurry. Come look!

232
00:19:06,970 --> 00:19:09,360
He's really handsome.

233
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:10,510
Hurry, hurry!

234
00:19:10,510 --> 00:19:12,790
Fine, fine.

235
00:19:12,790 --> 00:19:15,710
Only three seconds. I'll only look for three seconds.

236
00:19:21,770 --> 00:19:23,980
It's him.

237
00:19:23,980 --> 00:19:26,870
- It's been three seconds.
- Three seconds aren't enough! Thirty seconds.

238
00:19:26,870 --> 00:19:29,570
Who was it that just said this feels perverted?

239
00:19:29,570 --> 00:19:31,070
The words are still ringing in my ears.

240
00:19:31,070 --> 00:19:33,380
Do you feel like you've been slapped in the face?

241
00:19:44,180 --> 00:19:46,550
This is for you. I'll take this.

242
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:49,540
- So handsome!
- Zheng Xiao'en!

243
00:19:49,540 --> 00:19:52,410
He's really like the male protagonists in our romance novels.

244
00:19:55,050 --> 00:19:57,140
- Zheng Xiao'en!
- What?

245
00:19:57,140 --> 00:19:59,180
I bought that camera drone!

246
00:19:59,180 --> 00:20:01,650
Yours is mine. Mine is still mine.

247
00:20:01,650 --> 00:20:03,110
There's no such thing!

248
00:20:03,110 --> 00:20:05,260
Have you found the CEO?

249
00:20:05,260 --> 00:20:07,630
Yes! Over here!

250
00:20:13,190 --> 00:20:15,020
Hi!

251
00:20:15,020 --> 00:20:18,640
The CEO's winter outfit is also handsome!

252
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:23,330
From a very long time ago,

253
00:20:23,330 --> 00:20:26,000
he has been like a place of refuge to me.

254
00:20:48,850 --> 00:20:54,690
♫ Almost losing my soul ♫

255
00:20:54,690 --> 00:21:00,010
♫ Silently frozen like a statue ♫

256
00:21:00,010 --> 00:21:04,160
Setbacks. Everyone encounters various setbacks daily.

257
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,890
Including myself, of course.

258
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:09,730
And... maybe I encounter them more than others do.

259
00:21:09,730 --> 00:21:14,010
Really? Most people have the impression that you are a successful person born from a wealthy family.

260
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:16,620
You seem to be hardworking and optimistic.

261
00:21:17,540 --> 00:21:21,990
The me that everyone sees is the me that I'm willing to show everyone.

262
00:21:21,990 --> 00:21:26,090
Meaning that you have many other sides that not everyone sees?

263
00:21:27,050 --> 00:21:28,780
Of course.

264
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:31,100
Just like how you wouldn't show everyone

265
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:34,990
the images of you sitting on your couch eating a midnight snack, right?

266
00:21:36,220 --> 00:21:38,610
Then how do you face setbacks?

267
00:21:40,010 --> 00:21:42,220
Il faut être l'homme de la pluie

268
00:21:42,220 --> 00:21:44,660
et l'enfant du beau temp.

269
00:21:44,660 --> 00:21:47,990
In a storm, you have to be like an adult.

270
00:21:47,990 --> 00:21:51,160
In beautiful weather, you have to be like a child.

271
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:53,850
