513
00:40:04,810 --> 00:40:07,030
What about the truck company?

514
00:40:07,030 --> 00:40:10,370
I found the truck's delivery route. I'll send it to you.

515
00:40:11,380 --> 00:40:13,010
[Seven minutes to destination]

516
00:40:26,120 --> 00:40:29,480
Situ Aoran is so slow.

517
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:31,940
Is he riding a bike?

518
00:40:33,090 --> 00:40:35,820
A hero saving the damsel is so inefficient.

519
00:40:35,820 --> 00:40:39,550
By the time he comes, the female lead will already be dead!

520
00:40:42,890 --> 00:40:44,480
[Incoming Call]

521
00:40:46,720 --> 00:40:48,020
Hello?

522
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:50,390
Someone is trapped in the freezer. Stop the vehicle.

523
00:40:50,390 --> 00:40:52,390
I'm afraid she'll get hypothermia.

524
00:40:55,660 --> 00:40:57,630
Wait.

525
00:40:57,630 --> 00:41:00,360
I'm not the female lead.

526
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:03,490
Will no one come to save me?

527
00:41:04,250 --> 00:41:08,220
This truck! It won't stop!

528
00:41:08,220 --> 00:41:10,800
Drive to the coastal highway. The fewer people, the better.

529
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:14,870
The brakes aren't working! I'm afraid I won't be able to safely drive to the suburbs!

530
00:41:14,870 --> 00:41:17,470
It's useless to be afraid. You must drive.

531
00:41:17,470 --> 00:41:19,440
I'll go find you right away.

532
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:35,450
- Chuchu.
- How come you're here?

533
00:41:35,450 --> 00:41:37,340
Should I not be here?

534
00:41:37,340 --> 00:41:40,890
Didn't you go to get caviar and get trapped in the freezer truck?

535
00:41:40,890 --> 00:41:43,690
Did someone get trapped in the freezer truck?

536
00:41:49,490 --> 00:41:51,410
You have to accept your fate if you're not the female lead.

537
00:41:51,410 --> 00:41:53,380
Rough fish have to save themselves.

538
00:41:53,380 --> 00:41:55,960
The overbearing CEO hasn't fallen in love with me yet.

539
00:41:55,960 --> 00:41:58,370
I can't die here!

540
00:41:59,630 --> 00:42:04,990
Hey! Open the door!

541
00:42:06,240 --> 00:42:09,610
Help!

542
00:42:18,410 --> 00:42:19,570
Are the brakes still not working?

543
00:42:19,570 --> 00:42:21,390
It's not working. It won't brake!

544
00:42:21,390 --> 00:42:23,170
What about the handbrake?

545
00:42:23,170 --> 00:42:25,800
It's still no use!

546
00:43:09,490 --> 00:43:13,020
♫ Lost to you ♫

547
00:43:13,020 --> 00:43:21,270
♫ I think of you until I can no longer breathe ♫

548
00:43:21,270 --> 00:43:24,620
♫ My last wish is to never regret ♫

549
00:43:24,620 --> 00:43:30,660
♫ Brave out the heartbreak to no longer be afraid of heartbreaks ♫

550
00:43:30,660 --> 00:43:37,070
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

551
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:07,020
♫ The silhouettes of the concrete jungle ♫

552
00:44:07,020 --> 00:44:11,690
♫ All I see is you ♫

553
00:44:11,690 --> 00:44:13,620
You really came to save me.

554
00:44:13,620 --> 00:44:16,870
The brakes are not working. The truck could crash at any time.

555
00:44:16,870 --> 00:44:19,080
We have to get off quickly.

556
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:20,480
♫ Watching for the next morning ♫

557
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:23,630
♫ Nothing is impossible ♫

558
00:44:23,630 --> 00:44:27,980
♫ Even if no one is perfect ♫

559
00:44:27,980 --> 00:44:32,430
♫ Holding you next to my heartbeat ♫

560
00:44:32,430 --> 00:44:35,710
♫ Tightly held the palm of my hand ♫

561
00:44:35,710 --> 00:44:40,580
♫ It remains the only farewell ♫

562
00:44:40,580 --> 00:44:44,420
♫ If I could see you again ♫

563
00:44:44,420 --> 00:44:46,190
Are you ready?

564
00:44:46,190 --> 00:44:48,230
Ready for what?

565
00:44:48,230 --> 00:44:50,000
To jump off the truck.

566
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:52,690
How can you be ready for something like that?

567
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:56,430
Then don't be ready.

568
00:44:56,430 --> 00:45:05,540
♫ All of the innocent romance was lost to you ♫

569
00:45:05,540 --> 00:45:09,230
♫ If you were a painter ♫

570
00:45:09,230 --> 00:45:11,560
♫ Then I'll be your canvas ♫

571
00:45:11,560 --> 00:45:15,590
♫ Oh, lost to you ♫

572
00:45:15,590 --> 00:45:19,990
♫ I lost all my love to you ♫

573
00:45:33,420 --> 00:45:35,610
Are you alright?

574
00:45:37,620 --> 00:45:39,740
How can I be alright?

575
00:45:39,740 --> 00:45:41,780
I thought I was going to die!

576
00:45:41,780 --> 00:45:43,990
You didn't give me a warning before jumping.

577
00:45:43,990 --> 00:45:46,960
Even if I didn't die from the fall, I could've died from shock.

578
00:45:48,970 --> 00:45:53,070
I thought I was going to be buried with a bunch of dead fish eggs.

579
00:45:53,070 --> 00:45:57,050
Don't you know? You're the CEO!

580
00:45:57,050 --> 00:45:59,940
You have a cheat code! You have the power of being the male lead!

581
00:45:59,940 --> 00:46:03,140
You can do anything! You're great at everything! But I'm not! I'm nothing!

582
00:46:03,140 --> 00:46:06,990
I could actually die! Do you know that?

583
00:46:07,580 --> 00:46:11,530
If you want to hit me to vent your frustrations, you can.

584
00:46:12,920 --> 00:46:17,620
But can you hit this side instead?

585
00:46:17,620 --> 00:46:19,720
What?

586
00:46:20,890 --> 00:46:22,510
It hurts.

587
00:46:36,290 --> 00:46:38,020
You're not hitting me anymore?

588
00:46:39,190 --> 00:46:41,750
Since you're letting me hit you, I don't want to anymore.

589
00:47:15,750 --> 00:47:17,510
Do you feel a bit better?

590
00:47:29,320 --> 00:47:32,520
There's something I want to ask you.

591
00:47:32,520 --> 00:47:34,440
What is it?

592
00:47:36,060 --> 00:47:37,720
Chuchu...

593
00:47:39,280 --> 00:47:42,440
She's really not in that truck, right?

594
00:47:55,600 --> 00:47:58,050
Chuchu isn't in the truck.

595
00:47:58,050 --> 00:47:59,960
You don't have to worry.

596
00:48:22,720 --> 00:48:24,460
Don't get sick.

597
00:48:32,910 --> 00:48:35,120
Is your wound okay?

598
00:48:35,940 --> 00:48:38,140
Should you go to the hospital?

599
00:48:41,090 --> 00:48:45,380
Right now, there is something more important for me to do.

600
00:48:47,390 --> 00:48:49,030
Hey...

601
00:49:10,510 --> 00:49:12,840
Where is CEO Situ?

602
00:49:12,840 --> 00:49:16,720
It's the annual appreciation banquet today. How is he not present?

603
00:49:16,720 --> 00:49:19,470
Distinguished guests, please stay calm.

604
00:49:19,470 --> 00:49:21,910
The CEO went back to the company to handle some business.

605
00:49:21,910 --> 00:49:23,700
He will be here soon.

606
00:49:23,700 --> 00:49:28,560
On the table are delicacies that Royal Group carefully prepared for guests. Please enjoy.

607
00:49:28,560 --> 00:49:31,290
What business is more important than the appreciation banquet?

608
00:49:31,290 --> 00:49:33,900
There are no issues with the company's operations and finance, right?

609
00:49:33,900 --> 00:49:37,190
It's unusual that Situ Aoran hasn't showed up.

610
00:49:37,190 --> 00:49:40,470
Everyone should be cautious with their investment.

611
00:49:43,000 --> 00:49:45,590
CSO, what should we do?

612
00:49:45,590 --> 00:49:49,540
If the CEO does not show up soon, I'm afraid the investors will leave.

613
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:21,460
Exactly when is Situ coming?

614
00:50:21,460 --> 00:50:24,490
If he's not coming, don't waste our time!

615
00:50:24,490 --> 00:50:27,000
I don't care. I'm not waiting anymore.

616
00:50:33,890 --> 00:50:37,370
Everyone, sorry to keep you waiting.

617
00:51:03,980 --> 00:51:07,440
I'd like to welcome everyone to today's appreciation banquet.

618
00:51:07,440 --> 00:51:12,210
Next, I will report on Royal Group's profits from last year

619
00:51:12,210 --> 00:51:15,560
and our new plans for the next year.

620
00:51:15,560 --> 00:51:18,040
[Royal Group 2020 Mid-Year Report]
[Presented by Situ Aoran]

621
00:51:20,820 --> 00:51:25,010
[Hardware Engineering] [Transnational Agreements]
[Business Travel Accommodations] [Increasing Profits]

622
00:51:50,200 --> 00:51:52,510
[Investment Outcomes Over the Years]

623
00:51:53,540 --> 00:51:57,120
We will put all the information presented just now into an electronic file

624
00:51:57,120 --> 00:52:00,300
and send it to all the investors here today.

625
00:52:00,300 --> 00:52:02,470
Thank you, everyone.

626
00:53:15,080 --> 00:53:18,110
Your hair's all wet. Dry it.

627
00:53:19,010 --> 00:53:20,950
Thank you.

628
00:53:43,720 --> 00:53:46,050
Is something wrong?

629
00:53:46,050 --> 00:53:50,080
How did you know that Chuchu would be in danger?

630
00:53:51,040 --> 00:53:52,620
Did I?

631
00:53:52,620 --> 00:53:56,920
Stop faking. Chuchu already told me.

632
00:53:59,380 --> 00:54:02,730
Chuchu said you've been acting strange since yesterday.

633
00:54:02,730 --> 00:54:06,010
You wouldn't let her touch knives and forks or be near electrical wires.

634
00:54:06,010 --> 00:54:08,000
You wouldn't let her do anything.

635
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:10,080
You wouldn't even let her do things on her own.

636
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:13,270
Moreover, you kept warning her that she was in danger.

637
00:54:13,270 --> 00:54:17,610
You even predicted that she would trip. Why?

638
00:54:19,190 --> 00:54:21,570
Because...

639
00:54:22,770 --> 00:54:25,560
Because since I was little, I've always had a mysterious sense of what'll happen next.

640
00:54:25,560 --> 00:54:28,670
A sixth sense, déjà vu.

641
00:54:28,670 --> 00:54:30,770
Déjà vu?

642
00:54:30,770 --> 00:54:32,490
Déjà vu?

643
00:54:32,490 --> 00:54:34,250
That's right. That.

644
00:54:34,250 --> 00:54:36,180
Bullshit.

645
00:54:36,960 --> 00:54:38,290
Aoran?

646
00:54:38,290 --> 00:54:42,390
There's only one way she could know that Chuchu would be in danger.

647
00:54:42,390 --> 00:54:45,670
It's because she's the mastermind behind harming Chuchu.

648
00:54:49,040 --> 00:54:50,320
I'm the mastermind?

649
00:54:50,320 --> 00:54:52,190
Yes. It's you.

650
00:54:52,190 --> 00:54:55,000
Why is it me?

651
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:59,340
If it were me, then why was the person who was locked in the freezer truck me and not Chuchu?

652
00:54:59,340 --> 00:55:01,140
Because you're stupid.

653
00:55:01,140 --> 00:55:03,680
Dou E wasn't as wronged as I am.
(Character in the Chinese play "The Injustice to Dou E")

654
00:55:03,680 --> 00:55:06,430
I was locked in the freezer truck and forced to jump off the truck with you.

655
00:55:06,430 --> 00:55:08,450
Now, I'm even being blamed as the mastermind.

656
00:55:08,450 --> 00:55:11,940
Don't think that you can be this domineering just because you're an overbearing CEO.

657
00:55:11,940 --> 00:55:14,060
What Xiao'en said makes sense.

658
00:55:14,060 --> 00:55:16,710
I don't know what mistakes took place,

659
00:55:16,710 --> 00:55:19,600
but there is definitely a problem with Zheng Xiao'en.

660
00:55:19,600 --> 00:55:23,070
Forget it. You won't believe anything I say anyway.

661
00:55:23,070 --> 00:55:25,600
Okay, do you understand the presumption of innocence until proven guilty?

662
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:28,090
If you think that I was the one to set up Chuchu,

663
00:55:28,090 --> 00:55:30,630
then bring out the evidence that I was the assailant!

664
00:55:30,630 --> 00:55:33,500
Why is it flipped so that I have to prove my innocence?

665
00:55:33,500 --> 00:55:37,410
I have no evidence, but I have the basis.

666
00:55:37,410 --> 00:55:39,040
What basis?

667
00:55:39,040 --> 00:55:41,040
She has bullied Chuchu before.

668
00:55:42,100 --> 00:55:46,010
Zheng Xiao'en, it's because you've been previously convicted that I can't trust you.

669
00:55:46,010 --> 00:55:47,710
I already told you that it was a misunderstanding.

670
00:55:47,710 --> 00:55:50,100
Can't you give someone who's been reborn another chance?

671
00:55:50,100 --> 00:55:51,990
Another chance is something that others give you,

672
00:55:51,990 --> 00:55:54,760
not something that you can demand.

673
00:55:54,760 --> 00:55:57,030
You're just prejudiced against me.

674
00:55:58,880 --> 00:56:01,350
You want to prove your innocence, right?

675
00:56:01,350 --> 00:56:02,790
Okay!

676
00:56:02,790 --> 00:56:06,060
Starting now, you'll be the assistant to the Chief Strategy Officer.

677
00:56:06,060 --> 00:56:07,570
I'll have Qingfeng be in charge of watching you.

678
00:56:07,570 --> 00:56:10,010
Let's see what kinds of tricks you can play.

679
00:56:16,170 --> 00:56:19,560
♫ Lost to you ♫

680
00:56:19,560 --> 00:56:29,170
♫ I think of you until I can no longer breathe ♫

681
00:56:29,170 --> 00:56:31,330
♫ If you were a painter ♫

682
00:56:31,330 --> 00:56:34,640
♫ My last wish is to never regret ♫

683
00:56:34,640 --> 00:56:40,700
♫ Brave out the heartbreak to no longer be afraid of heartbreaks ♫

684
00:56:40,700 --> 00:56:47,330
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

685
00:56:48,500 --> 00:56:51,470
I can't believe he said that I was playing tricks.

686
00:56:51,470 --> 00:56:54,640
I'm telling you, I have a lot of tricks up my sleeve.

687
00:56:54,640 --> 00:56:56,620
Just you wait!

688
00:56:57,770 --> 00:57:01,820
Xiao'en, in the future, when you have time, we still have to eat lunch together.

689
00:57:01,820 --> 00:57:05,290
We'll see you in the break room. The gossip won't end.

690
00:57:06,190 --> 00:57:08,940
You have to take care of yourselves!

691
00:57:11,420 --> 00:57:14,340
Xiao'en, I'm sorry.

692
00:57:14,340 --> 00:57:16,860
It's all because I dragged you down.

693
00:57:16,860 --> 00:57:20,010
It's okay. There's no need to apologize.

694
00:57:30,500 --> 00:57:35,180
My beloved coworkers, I'm transferring to the strategy department now.

695
00:57:35,180 --> 00:57:37,080
Wait a second.

696
00:57:37,080 --> 00:57:38,950
Come with me.

697
00:57:45,240 --> 00:57:46,950
What is this?

698
00:57:46,950 --> 00:57:49,520
An affidavit. Sign it quickly.

699
00:57:49,520 --> 00:57:51,870
All of the clauses for confidentiality are on it.

700
00:57:51,870 --> 00:57:53,920
You absolutely can't sell us out.

701
00:58:01,710 --> 00:58:04,610
[Signed: Xiao'en]

702
00:58:17,940 --> 00:58:19,320
It's really heavy, right?

703
00:58:19,320 --> 00:58:20,980
Come with me.

704
00:58:25,380 --> 00:58:28,650
The standard nice guy is so considerate.

705
00:58:28,650 --> 00:58:32,370
Too bad you're the third wheel fated to not be loved.

706
00:58:37,060 --> 00:58:39,290
From now on, this is your seat.

707
00:58:39,290 --> 00:58:42,940
It's usually just me and Situ on this floor, but he's very busy.

708
00:58:42,940 --> 00:58:45,480
Now that you're here, there's finally someone to keep me company.

709
00:58:45,480 --> 00:58:48,590
Sorry, could you please repeat what you just said?

710
00:58:48,590 --> 00:58:50,060
There's finally someone to keep me company.

711
00:58:50,060 --> 00:58:52,050
The one before that.

712
00:58:52,820 --> 00:58:55,970
It's usually just me and Situ on this floor.

713
00:58:55,970 --> 00:58:59,220
That's it! Where is his desk?

714
00:59:02,880 --> 00:59:05,110
[Situ Aoran]

715
00:59:06,870 --> 00:59:08,430
Wow!

716
00:59:08,430 --> 00:59:12,390
Isn't this the legendary first row?

717
00:59:12,390 --> 00:59:14,360
Before, I could only use the drone to sneakily look.

718
00:59:14,360 --> 00:59:16,740
Now, it's real person VR.

719
00:59:16,740 --> 00:59:22,020
I basically went from the roof of Taipei Arena to the first row.

720
00:59:30,730 --> 00:59:32,530
What are you guys doing?

721
00:59:32,530 --> 00:59:33,930
The chairwoman is conducting an audit.

722
00:59:33,930 --> 00:59:36,520
We ask for your cooperation, Director Sun.

723
00:59:37,830 --> 00:59:40,070
I personally...

724
00:59:40,070 --> 00:59:42,300
Who are you? Why did you just barge in?

725
00:59:42,300 --> 00:59:43,700
Believe it or not, I will report you to the police!

726
00:59:43,700 --> 00:59:46,630
Director Zhang, as you secretly meet with contractors,

727
00:59:46,630 --> 00:59:52,020
perhaps you should think about how to explain yourself to the chairwoman instead of calling the police.

728
00:59:53,390 --> 00:59:55,710
Director Xu, please hold on. The chairwoman is still in a meeting.

729
00:59:55,710 --> 00:59:59,050
What meeting? Don't you know who I am? Beat it!

730
01:00:00,100 --> 01:00:02,010
Yes, I understand.

731
01:00:02,010 --> 01:00:03,730
That's great, He Mingli.

732
01:00:03,730 --> 01:00:08,040
Don't assume I don't know what you and Mr. Hu are scheming.

733
01:00:08,040 --> 01:00:11,280
Director Xu, what are you saying?

734
01:00:11,280 --> 01:00:14,500
The chairwoman and I are just discussing...

735
01:00:14,500 --> 01:00:18,870
whether we should have Chinese food or Western food for lunch today.

736
01:00:18,870 --> 01:00:21,670
He Mingli, think about it.

737
01:00:21,670 --> 01:00:25,210
If it were not for the few of us back then, would Tianliang have reached such a scale?

738
01:00:25,210 --> 01:00:28,720
What you're doing is the definition of ungrateful.

739
01:00:28,720 --> 01:00:33,360
If falsifying accounts and taking kickbacks express gratitude and loyalty,

740
01:00:33,360 --> 01:00:37,550
shouldn't I cut the weeds and dig up the roots for the good of Tianliang Group?

741
01:00:37,550 --> 01:00:39,890
Director Xu, if you have been honorable,

742
01:00:39,890 --> 01:00:41,590
what do you have to be afraid of?

743
01:00:41,590 --> 01:00:44,240
Don't think I'm actually afraid of you.

744
01:00:44,240 --> 01:00:46,400
Let's wait and see!

745
01:00:55,040 --> 01:01:00,460
Chairwoman, I understand your dilemma,

746
01:01:00,460 --> 01:01:06,430
but for some matters, it's best not to be too extreme.

747
01:01:06,430 --> 01:01:12,300
After all, these directors aren't to be reckoned with and aren't just there for display.

748
01:01:12,300 --> 01:01:17,780
What's wrong? You also object to how I do things?

749
01:01:17,780 --> 01:01:20,330
Chairwoman, no, don't misunderstand.

750
01:01:20,330 --> 01:01:24,370
I support you 100%.

751
01:01:28,460 --> 01:01:30,400
Chairwoman, we found it.

752
01:01:30,400 --> 01:01:34,720
The hospital said that CEO's personal belongings were taken away by Su Shanna.

753
01:01:34,720 --> 01:01:35,980
What about the will?

754
01:01:35,980 --> 01:01:38,540
It must also be with Su Shanna.

755
01:01:39,600 --> 01:01:42,510
We were even able to knock down her master.

756
01:01:42,510 --> 01:01:44,950
Are you afraid we can't take care of her?

757
01:01:51,520 --> 01:01:52,730
[Susan]
[Marketing Director]

758
01:01:52,730 --> 01:01:55,300
Okay, I got it. I'll give it to you tomorrow.

759
01:01:55,300 --> 01:01:57,040
Bye bye.

760
01:02:04,720 --> 01:02:07,620
Hey, what do you want to eat for lunch?

761
01:02:13,100 --> 01:02:15,110
What?

762
01:02:18,610 --> 01:02:22,520
Should we ask her if she wants to eat with us?

763
01:02:22,520 --> 01:02:25,050
Why ask her—

764
01:02:27,480 --> 01:02:32,280
Chuchu, do you want to eat lunch together?

765
01:02:32,280 --> 01:02:35,400
No, you guys go ahead.

766
01:02:50,140 --> 01:02:52,770
